<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,366,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Benetti &amp; Gustafson &amp; Hamada &amp; Short, 2020" authorityName="Benetti &amp; Gustafson &amp; Hamada &amp; Short" authorityYear="2020" box="[467,681,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequalis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[467,681,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">Hydaticus aequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[687,750,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[687,750,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique among Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1084,1198,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1198,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">Hydaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the general coloration in dorsal view almost evenly orange-brown and without elytral markings. Among the New World 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">Hydaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Benetti &amp; Gustafson &amp; Hamada &amp; Short, 2020" authorityName="Benetti &amp; Gustafson &amp; Hamada &amp; Short" authorityYear="2020" box="[211,340,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequalis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[211,340,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">H. aequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[347,411,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[347,411,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1863" box="[679,888,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piceus">
<emphasis box="[679,785,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">H. piceus</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
being reddish in color and having elytra without markings, however the latter belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[754,868,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,868,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="381">Hydaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s.str.)
</paragraph>
